Reasoning: The paper deals with the problem of certifying upper bounds on the maximum value of a quadratic form over a constraint set, which is a problem in optimization and computational complexity. The use of the Gaussian orthogonal ensemble and the negatively-spiked Wishart model suggests a connection to random matrix theory and information theory, which falls under cs.IT. The problem of certifying bounds on the Hamiltonian of the Sherrington-Kirkpatrick spin glass model is a problem in statistical physics, which can also be viewed as a problem in machine learning and data analysis, falling under cs.LG. The reduction from the Wishart detection problem suggests a connection to algorithms and data structures, falling under cs.DS. The use of low-degree polynomials suggests a connection to computational complexity theory, falling under cs.CC. Finally, the problem of certifying bounds on a quadratic form over a constraint set can also be viewed as a problem in control theory and systems engineering, falling under cs.SY.
